flowRoot.flowPara: These signs are using DIN 1451 font for German Road Signs, namely the Mittelschrift variant, and for narrow 100+ speeds using Engschrift
1. Use Inkscape editor and open the file
3. Menu "File" → Export (panel can be conveniently docked)
4. Ensure you are exporting "Selection" of square size
P.S. Font letter spacing might need to be adjusted (like 1 being off to the left and 5 being off-center too)
Image from Wikipedia for Minimal Speedlimit
Images from Wikipedia; Make sure signs have a shape which gives them contrast white outline
